Here is the complete plan I've designed after thoroughly reading the codebase.

---

## What I found

**Relevant file:** `common/chat.cpp` is the single file that needs to change.

**Architecture:** `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (~line 1634) is a dispatcher that inspects the raw Jinja template source for unique marker strings and routes to a dedicated static handler. All 7 current handlers live as static functions in the same file just above it.

**Key observation on Ministral 3 vs. v0.3:**
- Ministral 3 handler (line 1640) fires when `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` **is present** in the template source.
- A Mistral Instruct v0.3 Jinja template uses `[INST]`/`[/INST]` but has **no** `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — so the Ministral 3 check never fires for it, and the new handler can be distinguished purely by that absence.

---

## Two additions to `common/chat.cpp` (no other file touched)

### 1. New handler function (insert before `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`, ~line 1446)

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 - classic [INST]/[/INST] format
// Format: [INST] {user} [/INST]{assistant}</s>
// System message is prepended to the first user turn, separated by \n\n.
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

Uses `p.literal()` (not `p.prefix()`) because there's no optional thinking prefix — matching the same pattern as the `gigachat_v3` content-only branch.

### 2. Detection block (insert before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690)

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - [INST]/[/INST] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    // Absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT] distinguishes this from Ministral/Magistral Large 3.
    if (src.find("[INST]")          != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]")         != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

